r2914 | jaudoux | 2014-09-09 17:01:30 +0200 (mar. 09 sept. 2014) | 6 lignes

Extraction of GkArrays library from CRAC core:
- We can now use any ReadIndex we want by just creating a new class inheriting from "ReadIndex" and declaring a support(Read*r) method
- The parrallelization has changed in order to use the new Read object
- locateServer is out of order waiting for an implementation that can use the new abstract ReadIndex instead of GkArrays
- :) yes this is a huge commit, but it is a lot of fun too ;)

